<p>
Northeastern University, Boston, MA. Assistant Professor, tenure track,
beginning September 2010. Department of Philosophy and Religion. Area of
Specialization: Philosophy of Science or Philosophy of Social Science. Area
of Competence: Ethics. Ph.D. required by time of appointment. Teaching
experience preferred. Typical teaching load is two courses per semester.
The department seeks candidates with strong scholarly promise and a strong
commitment to undergraduate teaching. Review of applications will begin
immediately and continue until the position is filled. Applications
received by Dec. 19 will be assured full consideration. To apply, please
visit the college website, <a href="http://www.northeastern.edu/cas/" rel="external">http://www.northeastern.edu/cas/</a>, and click on
Faculty Positions. On-line applications should include a cover letter with
a description of research interests and teaching experience, a curriculum
vitae, evidence of teaching effectiveness (where appropriate), and a sample
of scholarly writing. In addition, applicants must have at least three
confidential letters of reference sent directly to: Philosophy of Science
Search, Department of Philosophy and Religion, 371 Holmes Hall,
Northeastern University, Boston, MA 02115. All other materials should be
submitted online. Questions about the position may be addressed to Ronald
Sandler, Chair of the Search Committee, at <a href="mailto:r.sandler@neu.edu" rel="email">r.sandler@neu.edu</a> or
617.373.3619. Northeastern University is an Equal Opportunity, Affirmative
Action Educational Institution and Employer, Title IX University.
Northeastern University particularly welcomes applications from minorities,
women and persons with disabilities.
